@@ -40,1 +40,1 @@
-# Included files, as well as files pointed by java.security.properties,
+# Included files, as well as files pointed to by java.security.properties,
@@ -47,5 +47,0 @@
-# System properties in included paths provide flexibility for users to
-# switch between predefined security profiles on a per-execution basis.
-# Profile selection may be required or optional depending on the files
-# layout, as shown in example #3 below.
-#
@@ -62,9 +57,0 @@
-# In example #3, if Java is launched with the argument -DSecurityProfile=FIPS,
-# the profile defined in profileFIPS.security is applied. An error is thrown
-# if this file is not found. Other files may exist in the same directory,
-# enabling the selection of alternative profiles. If SecurityProfile is not
-# set, it expands to the empty string. When a profile.security file exists
-# (may be empty), it defines a default security profile. When it does not,
-# an error is thrown and explicit profile selection is required. In order
-# to override properties defined in this file, the include statement may be
-# placed at the end.
